<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ruspolii" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruspolii" status="stat. nov.">Convolvulus ruspolii</taxonomicName>
Dammer ex Hallier f., Ann. Reale Inst. Bot. Roma 7: 225. 1898. (
<bibRefCitation author="Hallier, H" journalOrPublisher="Annuario del Reale Istituto Botanico di Roma" pageId="203" pageNumber="204" pagination="223 - 236" refId="B147" refString="Hallier, H, 1898b. Contribuzioni alla conoscenza della flora dell' Africa orientale XVIII Convolvulaceae. Annuario del Reale Istituto Botanico di Roma 7: 223 - 236" title="Contribuzioni alla conoscenza della flora dell' Africa orientale XVIII Convolvulaceae." volume="7" year="1898 b">Hallier 1898b</bibRefCitation>
: 225). Type. ETHIOPIA, Ogaden, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Riva</emphasis>
297 (holotype FT!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus ruspolii" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruspolii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Convolvulus ruspolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dammer ex Hall f.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ruspolii" subSpecies="hystrix">subsp. hystrix</taxonomicName>
in armature but the spine-like side branches rather slender. Stems glabrous to shortly pubescent. Leaves 5-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, oblong or lanceolate to elliptic, glabrous to puberulent or sericeous. Flowers usually solitary, sometimes in pairs forming a narrowly oblong-lanceolate head twice as long as broad; bracteoles 3-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 mm, oblong, oblanceolate or obovate, longer than broad; corolla 0.8-1 cm long. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sebsebe, D" editor="Hedberg, I" journalOrPublisher="National Herbarium Addis Ababa University &amp; Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala University" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="161 - 231" refId="B330" refString="Sebsebe, D, 2006. Convolvulaceae. In: Hedberg, I, Ensermu, K, Edwards, S, Sebsebe, Demissew, Persson, E, Eds., Flora of Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea 5: Gentianaceae to Cyclocheilaceae. National Herbarium Addis Ababa University &amp; Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala University: 161 - 231" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea 5: Gentianaceae to Cyclocheilaceae." year="2006">Sebsebe 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 182]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Ogaden region of Ethiopia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Hemming</emphasis>
1530) and Somalia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Popov</emphasis>
1008; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Glover &amp; Gilliland</emphasis>
636; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Thulin &amp; Warfa</emphasis>
5562; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Bally</emphasis>
10164).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Some specimens from Somalia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Gillett, Hemming &amp; Watson</emphasis>
21885, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Bally &amp; Melville</emphasis>
16271, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Thulin &amp; Warfa</emphasis>
5562, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Kasmi et al.</emphasis>
850) have ellipsoid flower clusters with 2-4 flowers and are intermediate with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ruspolii" subSpecies="hystrix">subsp. hystrix</taxonomicName>
and suggestive of hybrid origin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
